content: Fantastic
Doesn't work,i paid ¬£4 for nothing
Unfortunately does not work on my android 2020 model. Programme last updated in 2018. Shame as could be very useful if updated and compatible with Android updates
easy to use, could feature more variety of foods. Why don't you feature wholegrain rice and pasta options for chili and pasta combined dishes ? Or some way of picking favourites?
Always works fine for me over the last 4 or 5 years I've had it. Not all foods are on there but easy to google what you need.

Quite an indepth app, needs lots of attention but the results are worth it. A conversion from carbs to units of insulin per food & totalled per meal would be great. This helps to show where your insulin is being used & why/ when a hypo/ hyper could occur.
Okay, ancient design, slow and unoptimised. The actual data is mostly there and fairly accurate though.
Waste my $$ bs selection of limited food
The android app is only half as good as the apple version. Why? Why can't we have the same up to date version especially as I've paid for this app.
It really is as out dated as everyone has described
I bought the app now says it won't work without an update but no update available!!!!!!!!!! Sort it out. Was a good app otherwise and would have given a 4 not 1

Been using this app for 4 years now and is generally very good but now discovering annoying limitations on available reasons for adding a test result. Only options surround meal times and bed, it would be nice to have the ability to add my own reason for blood test like "before drive" for example or something else. I can appreciate the app is based around food therefore meal times option makes sense but not a great choice for general diabetes result logging. Add in the ability for notes please.
Needs 2020 update
App doesn't load up just keeps closing. Also loads of stuff missing off the app. For the price you would expect something much better.
Needs updating like asap
Do not cover all food especially Pakistani and indian food. No mention of glycemic index.
It would be great if you could put your own weight in or even if there was a per 100g option to help us T1 mums and dads work out the insulin.

Last update was 2018, no replies to emails! This is very lazy and evidences a lack in development. Many common foods are missing or it is fussy regarding food names. This could easily be resolved with more variables and again evidences lazy development. It's also slow to use and states "downloading" every time launched. The included basal bolus system is useless, you have to manually calculate carbs and there isn't anywhere to input a correction ratio, or reduction ratios for exercise etc.

Brilliant app was recommended to get it by doctor at the hospital as I'm diabetic to help me count carbs on what I eat and it's great, it also tells you the fat content, calories and protein for different portion sizes on quite a range of different foods and takeaways. Would definitely recommend

Good idea but outdated. Given the current technology this app could be improved further. For example, link with online database, such as calories king and so on. Healthcare workers encouraged me to use the app, but I don't find myself beneficial from it because the database is limited.

I purchased this on the recommendation of a nutritionalist. It doesn't work. It didn't allow me to set up my details, the videos on the website don't match the screens on the app. I can't get a refund. I feel totally duped. Don't buy it

Android Phone? - Don't Bother! Being taught to use this app in the hospital to manage my newly diagnostic child, I was horrified to find that once discharged from the hospital and left to "go solo", everything that I had learnt was void as the app you rely so heavily on, doesn't actually work on android. Extremely disappointed that I paid my money in good faith for this app, only to discover that it does not have half the foods and you cannot change your weights to get exact carbohydrates.

I saw thought that this app would be Perfect for helping me to control my type 1 diabetes but it just does not contain enough info on uk foods. I therefore, cannot give a higher rating. Check out weights of anything on toast 737g not! When will you update and rectify. This is , after all, a paid for app.
This app is not working.. It's not showing up recipes. It's only asking for my recipes
Disappointing compared to the Apple version. Looks very dated.
Love the app works for me as a diabetic however the new update removed all the food examples and made the app unusable except got my own recipes and foods
Useful information, but the pictures of portion sizes are usually distorted and not that helpful.
Good App

Compared to the iphone app this is appalling. Ive relied on the app for my diabetes for a long time changed to android an im really strugling. Can u not update this to same as iphone.. would make life sooooo much easier.
Must have for all type 1 diabetics who carb count.
Not what expecting 2019 one only

Harder to use than the iPhone version. The iPhone app let's you tap in the weight of your choice and add to meals, so easy. Asked for a refund as it takes too long to use. I will stick to the iphone app.

Good app with a good variety of food choices. It is however annoying that you can't choose more than one thing at once when adding foods. Would be great to have that option so you don't have to keep going back and forth, when you have to choose a variety of vegetables for instance.

The app tries to second guess what you might eat. For example if you search Dahl you get Dahl with sweet potatoes and naan, so if you want dahl without sweet potato and naan you are stuffed. I am diabetic, and this is better than nothing, although it would be more helpful if, as in the example above, dahl, sweet potatoes and naan were all listed separately.
Not worth the money I've had this app for a few years now and have never really found it that useful i was expecting it to expand regularly but everytime i go to look something up it's never there
Diabetes type two with insulin
Currently won't work at all.
Very helpful

Difficult to use, not intuitive and I've gone back to alternative after two days. Also finding the values for previous entries is tedious. Whilst picture are handy, it should also give you opportunity to enter food by weight too.
Pretty dreadful app. Looks like it's from 2010
Was very useful for carb calculations. I'm Diabetic and it's pretty accurate.
Out of date
Built for older android versions. Not worth the money. My fitness pal has more and better examples

Used to love this app. Installed it onto a new phone and now when I click onto it, it just downloads the directory and freezes. Frustrating when you need to eat and you cannot find the info you need...grrrrr

Not worth ¬£3.99 if you already have the book - I already got the book a while ago and thought I would get the app in case there were updated foods etc and was initially pleased when I saw it tracks meals too. However, the tracker is poor and while there are more food items than the book, there aren't that many that I would use. For free with Samsung (on my phone), you get their own Health app - which I find sooo much better than this one in terms of food selections, info and user-friendliness.

Compared to the iPhone version, this is lacking. The iPhone version let you input custom weights which really helped whereas this version, for whatever reason, doesn't allow that. Fair enough you can choose multiples of an item, but thats not as easy as being able to input the exact weight of food you have and getting an exact reading. For me personally this was a waste of money, and if you're diabetic looking for exact carb measurements, this isn't the app for you, unless youre on iPhone.
Very useful for diabetics
Great app

This app could do with an update, (last updated 22nd May 2018) especially as people pay for it. There are loads and loads of food items not listed, basic everyday items. They could collaborate with Slimming World and include an exhaustive list of foods.

Life saver I was recently diagnosed with type 1 diabetes and this app was recommended by my diabetes team, and all I can say is its fab! It made carb counting for my insulin so simple took me all of 5 minutes to figure it out and now I use it throughout the day, such a massive help as it isn't always easy with 3 kids to be sat doing maths to give insulin right on top of meal times
Helps me daily

I have used the Carbs & Cals App for nearly 2 years since my Type 2 diabetes diagnosis and it has been a lifesaver! Having just changed my phone, I downloaded this latest version...it is AWFUL!!! It is so much harder to use. The sliding scale for portion size means you're guessing all the time rather than putting in the actual weight/volume; the daily overview is daunting to look at .......... I've gone back to the previous version and so have to carry 2 phones around! PLEASE, PLEASE GO BACK !
Good idea

Doesn't work. I spent 10 minutes downloading the food database after installation but it won't even search for crumpets or tea. I've paid for this app twice because it doesn't have a user login. If you change your phone, be prepared to pay again and start from the beginning. I'm requesting a refund.
Good. But app is old and buggy. Not been updated in years and is showing its age, will not be long untill it's incompatible with newer version of Android.

This should be an incredible resource for health care professionals and patients just like the app available to apple users on iphones, however, as evident by the fact that they are still using the old icon and the amount of bugs and lack of features - it needs a major update. Patients with diabetes shouldn't have to be locked out of accessing what would be an incredible resource, just because they have an android phone instead of an apple one.
Big improvements since last update
replyContent: We are sorry you are experiencing problem.  The issue is due to a recent Google update, which has affected a large number of apps on the Play Store.  This issue is not due to the Carbs & Cals app.  We are waiting for Google to issue a fix for all the apps that have been affected.

content: It does need work. I'm in the UK but when setting up I couldn't deselect food images for Austria. Why?? Also, when setting targets I had to abandon as buttons were greyed out, yet I couldn't continue without selecting them. As for using the app, presentation is good, but the range of foods is much more limited than another app I use.
Seems fairly concise. I use it as reference for my type 1 diabetes
I download app but in my phone portion are not come in 6 different portions Its come 1 or 3 Nor i change gms settings Why this happens? Plz check

Its like using a computer software from the early 90s completely outdated , could not even find Kellogg's shreddies what is a very well known cerial in Uk, this App should be updated because customers have to pay for it, and especially to help the type 1 diabetic community as this is very IMPORTANT
Excellent
I ve already purchased this but i needed to factory reset my phone and now it wants me to pay again. Help?!

What the hell happened! So whilst yes there was a limited database now I have no database. No access to any foods unless I put it all in myself. I didn't pay for that. You've made the app confusing as hell.

This app should be studied as a counter-example of good design: - Entering data (blood sugar levels) does not necessarily store it. - Hitting back on the list of foods throws you out of the app, no matter how you ended up there. - Overall, it is not obvious how to enter data or do anything: what should be the main menu, is a tiny drop-down at the top right. - When the app opens, there is a pause of some seconds while "downloading" some database. It apparently never finishes...
Was hoping this would be great. Sadly not! Gives basic info but doesn't alter carbs when grams is changed.
Used to be the best app for my diabetes, however this does not work on my new huawei p30 pro. Updates clearly required urgently!!
Outdated. Can barely find name brand foods in the look up. Have to manually enter it.
Good app as I use to count carbs as I'm a type 1 diabetic. However when I had an iPhone you could put the weight of food in but with android you can't.
Why why this app is rubbish on Android but work great on Apple version?? You should do the same Apple version on Android? Am not happy with this app on Android version! Please change it!!
Would be 5 star if they added more foods and grouped them. Cant even add fish and chips (takeaway) and theres a fair few things that are not uncommon foods that are missing
Does not add up carbs as you enter weight. It works on iPhone so why not android.

Carbs and calieries Yes I bought this but have not been given this every time it tells me to buy again can you please get this downloaded ASAP and I have complained about this on many occasions and nothing has been done to help with this but it was about 4-5 years ago please help me get this sorted for the last time I‚Äôm requesting this Thank you if I actually get this sorted

I was advised to install this app after attending a diabetic training course. It's extremely limited compared to other apps and totally different on Android compared to the demo I saw on Apple. I'll be sticking to the usual app I use as it's far more beneficial to me and my carb counting requirements.
My son is type 1 and this is a fantastic app it's very helpful especially when eating out.
Brilliant app for keeping a track on my carbs.
A complete waste of time, I spent so long trying to putin my birth date; it's too inconvenient, I would like a full refund.

Absolutely frustrating tried putting my date of birth in 9 bloody times am I missing something? Scrolling back 48 fricking years why can't we just enter digits. I've just come out of hospital with diabetes problems and thought this app was a good idea. I'm sure it wasn't this flimsy and backward before. A total waste of bloody time. I will stick to pen and paper thanks NOT IMPRESSED gutted that I even gave it 1 star. The imput of data on the dob should not have to be scrolled back on.
Just reinstalled this app, why does the ios version have much better features and interface???
Rubbish. Type 1 diabetic. Missing loads of foods that are on ios version and missing loads of functionality from ios version. Absolute guff!!! DO NOT BUY!!!!!!!!
Labour intensive
Paid for the app. No meal , snack , food data available under any category. Am I doing something wrong?
Much less user friendly than the iOS version. A shame as it could be so much better.
Very good

This is best available. Easy to navigate. Pictures of portions makes it easy to calculate your carb intake. Although it doesn't have "every" food item, still a good variety. I use this app a lot. Anything that helps manage Type 1 Diabetes is worth using

I've always bought the books in the past & loved them so I thought I'd go digital and have it with me all the time. Sadly no the app is missing so many items and what's worse when it does show what you are looking for there is a good chance that the nutritional information will be missing. My advise if avoid the app and get a book instead
Really needs an update

Very disappointed, very basic and for me worst purchased ever. Furthermore in other apps you can ask for a refund inside the app without to ask Google for the refund but not in this one. As you do not get a trial and it is difficult to get a refund II advise you to think deeply before you buy it.
Functionality on android is rubbish, I really wish I hadn't wasted my money.

The app is ok but the apple version is a million times better considering it's a pay for app I do think it should have the same features as the apple version I'd rather pay the ¬£1 more to get the features

Really disappointed with the Android version of the app. The app on Apple is so much better. You can't change the weight like you do with an Apple phone. You have to stick with the pre-set portions. Rubbish!

This app is really helpful, but I wish it was kept up to date. There's tons of food items that are different to the latest book, which has lead to underestimating the carbs in my food. Please can you update the app to have the more correct carbs! (And the features that the apple version has would be nice too! :P)
Good app, just waiting for more restaurants to be added for Android, particular nandos. Apple already have this facility

Very disappointed that I cannot use this off-line, despite downloading the pictures several times while on wifi at home. As soon as i try to see them when off-line they are not there. Useless for me and a waste of money.
The ios version much better
Not very useful I am now diabetic and disappointed
App stopped worked they are refusing a refund. Stay clear!!!!!!!!!!!

The iOS version is better for adding foods and having a dashboard. Looks nicer as well. But doesn't have the diabetes section. Android version can't be backed up. May be an issue if phone needs resetting as all the custom food would need adding again. Luckily I have both versions of the app so I can keep the custom food in the iPad, but this is poor. Saving to Drive would be a suitable upgrade. Why can't both apps be the same. Although the iOS app costs ¬£1 more.
Waste of money, very limited choices of food for UK.  I would have spent forever updating it.
PLEASE can android users have the custom weight option???
It's not updated and, after checking the CP in here, i ended up with an hypoglycemia at work. Please update it!
it is not as good as the book
This needs updating for android!

the IOS version is much better than the Android, in addition that you simply can't choose how many grams of the bread for example.. u have to choose either 1, 1/2, or3/4 , and the lack of barcode scanner.. and its not user friendly.. there are no trial period and based on my IOS version i bought it..but i am very disappointed.. yet i didn't refund as i hope the developer will acutely do something about it..

why have you put black writing against a very dark grey background when choosing a portion size. I have eyesight problems and have difficulty reading news print so this is impossible. even an eagle would not be able to read this. is the person who thought of this related to superman. unless this is rectified then I will not be able to use this app and will have wasted good money on an inferior app.
The basic idea and functionality of this app is valuable for diabetics; a searchable database of foods with carb info. The app feels dated and unmaintained, but is still useful.

A great Idea, but could be better. I can't seem to find a way to edit what I have put in. Also not every food option is there, so sometimes I have to add the closest. That said, the app calculates the amount of fat, carbs etc and what you have remaining from your daily allowance.
Very disappointing compared to same app on iPhone. Don't understand why it didn't have the same content?? ü§î‚òπÔ∏è
It doesn't work and I bought it
very limited food options, needs lots more adding to the app

I started to use the app yesterday as well as others based on recom. from my dietitian. The intention is good but if I'm paying for it I'd expect a lot more than what it is. Why it doesn't update amounts straight away of Carbs, Cals, Fat etc. if I change the amount to 2 or 3/4 or any really? Food that I eat daily is not included such as sourdough, various yoghurts and fruits. Maybe you could give space to add foods with nutrition.values for each user themselves. I'm disappointed.
need cloud save or backup for my foods. also needs recent and better search type the wrong word first wont find anything. IPhone app looks much better
very good gives a guide to what you are eating and how it effects your diabetes. Needs some work to make it easier to use.

I use an android phone & though this app would be an alternative to carrying the book. It doesn't work! I cant search good, it only lets me add food & wants me to give the nutrition for the food!! I'm very disappointed & I paid for this app.
Very good it is like the ios versien but on android
All the information

i brought this app to use as I'm diabetic it was working alright on my android 7 phone i have now upgraded my android phone to android 9 and this app no longer works properly it doesn't load i tried many times to download it could you please update this app so i can use it as it's been helpful for me and a Shame that i can't use it

This app is a total waste of time on my android phone. I tried to download all images but the app keeps deleting all the downloads. On good WiFi areas a lot of the images appear with a question mark in place of images you have selected. I can't use this app in poor WiFi areas at all. I am a type 1 diabetic and very disappointed with this app. Why is the seller of this app being allowed to advertise it as something great when it does not work on android phones.
the android version is incredibly poor when compared to the apple version...needs an urgent update
this app is amazing unfortunately the people moaning arent technical sound. nothing wrong with it works like a dream worth every penny.
Awful and clunky compared to the iOS version, with none of the iOS features.It's not free, so the same amount of effort should be put into creating a decent android app.
This app is a God send, very helpful, especially when out for meals as it has pictures of portions rather than weights

Really useful app when eating out or guesstimating. However my husband downloaded it on his iPhone when my phone was dead once and to my surprise it is much more up to date and has much more food/portion options on there, very disappointing for me as a Samsung user. Just dont understand why you wouldn't update both versions, Samsung diabetics need accurate blood control too üôÑ
very helpful

Needs more developement. Not easy to add items to meals once they are saved. Amounts could include the options of the number of servings or cup full. This would be useful for some items. btw I'm using Moto G6. Update. I do get a bit frustrated with this app at times. With a bit more thought it could, potentially, be very good. I would like to see some additions; a category to record what Ive, drunk and although you can set a target weight, you cannot record this to monitor your progress.
excellent. useful. glad I came across it.
deals with real foods, rather than brand names!
Completely broken on Android.

got the app cos i needed it for my diabetes management. however this version is not the same as seen in pics above or on my friends phone. so have not got any of the features they have like all the named takeaway and restaurants with their recipe info. what a waste of moneyüò°

i yse this app as im a diabetic so i need to allways see my blood sugar results i stated to use on my tablet abd later to my phone .. my question why dont they sync o have samsung tablet and phone i cant get them to sync ... nit happy

I used this very effectively on my previous phone so I'm disappointed that there is no facility to transfer my history and personal foods data to the app once I have installed it on my new phone.
what an outdated and inaccurate app, considering its a payable app its got no barcode scanner and the whole look of it is dated. not impressed.

Very disappointed. App was recommended by a health professional, but she clearly had the ios version. the android version is clunky, non-intuitive and very basic. Looked on the website for tutorial, but videos must be for ios as the bear no resemblance to the android version. if you're a reputable company you should update ir refund.
there's a lot of foods and drinks that aren't on here constantly having to add foods on here and it's a pain

Great app that can be used with or without the book. App could do ewth some further development, but is up there with more expensive apps from global dietary companies. This app was recommended to me by a hospital nutritionist as it allows you to balance calories, fats, sugars, fibre and excercise. Well done.
not great needs more.
Have been using this app for carb counting for my sons diabetes but the last few days hasn't worked what so ever doesn't even open properly not impressed in the slightest
Great app, tells you what you are eating carbs, cals, fat, fibre and all

This app was recommended by the diabetes nurse to help control my T2 diabetes. Paid and downloaded app to find that many pictures have not download so many categories useless. The ones that are working are great.

Overall a decent app and helpful for my type 1 diabetes. However when entering carbs and insulin doses the " diabetes diary " section of the app always displays different carbs amounts to the amounts which I have entered
DO NOT BUY THIS UNFINISHED APP! No support. Invalid contact email address.
This app is very poor. Some categories are blank. A request for help from support has been ignored. Do NOT BUY! i repeat... no support! unfinished app! DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY!
great for diabetics
superb

Bit complicated Why in this day & age can't you put your birthday in by simply typing dd/m/yy. I do not appreciate tapping all the way back to the 40's!! I don't find the app all that easy to work..instructions would be good. It has the potential to be great, but not there yet.

Really disappointed that it is not the same as the version available on apple. With a recent diagnosis of type 1 diabetes in the family this was recommended to us by the hospital but you cannot input the weight of food like you can on apple. Really frustrating when I need this at home and I only have android. Please update!

What size is the plate used. Portion sizes of potatoes, pasta etc not realistic to weight quoted. Can we have portion sizes as a percentage or 1/3rds (3 grown ups regularly in our house) not going to divide by 1/4 multiples...

worst app ever especially dealing with a type one diabetic, the IOS app is amazing and helps so much please update to IOS standards!!!
Excellent well laid out. Easy to use.

techinically its all here but this is a very very VERY clumsy app with appalling sloppy design interface. Nothing does what it says. the "workflow" is non existent the terms and choices make no sense at any time. in order to EAT AN APPLE you can't simply pick a food save it / you HAVE to (menu) "calendar&excercise" > "diary" > "edit" > (menu again, there is no button) > (click pen by the word) "snack" > (via main menu again, there is no button) > "meal" > "edit" > "add food"> "Search" ..
Good app very helpful
cant even open the app that it crashes and stopps working. please help fix this!

It's exactly the same as the old book. My son is type 1 diabetic so we need to calculate the carbs with each meal. It is handy that I don't need to carry the book around but it's not as good as the iOS version. Unfortunately you can't put in the weight of the food so still need to use a calculator. Such a shame the android version isn't as useful as the iOS version. Do you know if this function will be coming to the android version?

very disappointing the app isn't updated when new books come out. saying we pay for the app it's the least that should be expected. disappointing when you see people post things you wonder about. Please update the app
I can't set up my targets it won't let me put my DOB in
amazing. more options and better way for accuracy

Desperately needs updating, it's now 2019... New book is now even getting old... New iOS app was out ages ago... How about bringing this elderly android app up to the same level? Or can't you be bothered? We are being treated as 2nd class users?

My partner has the app on iPhone which is brilliant. This is not the same! Our child has type1 diabetes and the most important feature is changing the weight of the item which converts the amount of carbs per gram. The Android version is useless in relation to my needs and I feel ripped off

Running this app on Android. As many people have said it desperately needs an update. Contacted developers three times requesting timetable for Android update. No response! With diabetes so much in the news great opp. for someone else to delevop a better app. for Android hopefully.
needs fixing photo keep disrepairin when downloadeding lots not working on this app sad it could be a great app if it worked

wanted to share this as a family app, to my 11 year old daughter, who is type 1 diabetic, and now old enough to take over management, but i can't because i bought it before 2016. People who bought after that date are fine. I feel robbed, because i can't even buy it again.

would be a lot better if there was a barcode scanner to add foods instead of having to manually input them
nothing works on Android
No use on Android for diabetics: you can't weigh and enter serving sizes as you can on iOS

I've found this app extremely useful for calculating rapid insulin doses. The only thing I wish it has would be a 'my meals' section along side the 'my foods'. Would enable the user to calculate insulin dose at a glance
Liked the app but am on holiday in Spain and doesn't have paella or tapas could this be added please as really struggling to find the carbs of things I can eat here thanks
Android version is way out of date and can't add own portion sizes. With a new diagnosis for a child I need to be able to use this out and about.... Please hurry up and update or refund please!

This app doesnt seem to be working with Android 9. Searching for anything (e.g. banana) does not show any results, downloading images for offline use doesn't change this. This is unfortunate as this app seems to be the only option for showing image estimates alongside carb counts. I hope the developer invests some time into this (from the ground up rewrite is needed) as there is clearly a need for this.
Doesn't have a majority of food you look for, it's good for recording blood glucose readings but if you want something to check carbs in food then my fitness pal is free and much better.
Could larger food base or allow you to scan barcode of product or input weight of something as pics arent clear

Good app in theory, but poor in practice. The facility to store images on the device for offline use does not work. This means that if there is no Internet connection available, the app is useless. This has never worked for the 4 years that I've owned the app and it's a disgrace that it's not been fixed yet. Waste of money.

How the heck are you supposed to plug in your sugar ranges? It keep referring back to some stupid number no matter what you put in.....can you fix this now? Don't want half the job done. I've paid for this and it's not working 100%
Handy tool for tracking cals etc throughout the day highly recommend,good for diabetics too

Someone has already commented on 2/10/18 that the Android version is behind the IOS version. I've just switched phones and was also very disappointed to discover this. Many people find it necessary to be able to quickly add their own food portion sizes for a quick result. You won't be able to do that with this app, instead you'll be switching between the app and your calculator while the rest of the family are tucking in to their meal. Poor, am looking in to other options.
Nothing like the description, this was the Android version so cannot comment on the apple version, waste of money.
quick and easy to use so much better than carrying a book around with me

App has been neglected. No updates, biggest problem is there is an error where the pictures don't load. You therefore can't use it to estimate carb values based on pictures. Diabetics rely on this app and you are letting us down by neglecting this app, if you can't maintain it, remove it from the store.

This app is not worth ¬£4. It is terrible to navigate, badly designed and frustrating to use. Wish I hadn't bothered. You can't put ingredients measurements easily, trying to make your own recipes is not straightforward, and is hard work and confusing. Navigating the app is confusing and easy to get lost, as it doesn't do thing in a logical order. I would like my money back, but because I used it for 2-3 day it no longer give me the option.

Great app but the Android version is way behind the iPhone version! On Android version there is much less flexibility with portions and the exercise function DOESN'T WORK - it's rubbish and takes hours of fiddling to register the right number of calories burned. No excuse when it all works so well on the iPhone version. Get it sorted and I will love it again.
I wish we could have the iPhone version of this app! It's so much better!

Please add per 100g weight reference values. It could just be an option within the portion quantities or an additional portion size. So much more useful if you decide to weigh your portions for accuracy. I am disappointed that this feature isn't already available, now having to pay for this app. Otherwise, thanks for providing a fantastic resource for diabetics and the like, and it could easily be even more useful!
Pretty useless app for me as couldn't find most of the foods I was looking for so was guessing the carb content when out recently in a restaurant.
It does not work, no pictures/photos, waste of money and time so I am uninstalling it. I'll just stick with the book which is fantastic.

Food library very poor. Recipe section appears to only allow you to save one ingredient! Can't copy breakfast to the next day so have to put the whole thing in every morning. Same with other meals. Very frustrating and irritating to use. Bizarrely, the book has a better food library. Very disappointed.
The database is so old and lacks some of the common foods like pasta and sushi. Come one guys, modernise or die..

replyContent: We are sorry you are experiencing problem.  The issue is due to a recent Google update, which has affected a large number of apps on the Play Store.  This issue is not due to the Carbs & Cals app.  We are waiting for Google to issue a fix for all the apps that have been affected.

I use this for counting carbs as part of diabetes control. It's a small tool in a complex management job, and it has great potential.   However, it is let down by what seems to be a total lack of maintenance/development. How about a "pro" or "plus" version, or subscription features? - I would *very* happily pay more for a significantly enhanced app.   PROS:  It does the basic job *really* well. The database behind the app is a good start, custom foods mean it is possible to set up for foods not on the database.   CONS: integration with / sharing of data with other apps (e.g. GLIMP) is missing and is an absolute essential for me.  CONS: Food database needs cloud integration so that custom foods can be saved/shared. Food database needs massively expanding (and opening up to user submissions). Barcode scanning needed. As per other reviews, searching of the database for foods is poor.
